<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/CountingUnit> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/CountingUnit> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "\n  <p>A <em>Counting Unit</em> is used for all units that express counts. \n  Examples are Atomic Number, Number, Number per Year, Percent and Sample per Second.\n  </p>\n  "^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#HTML> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/CountingUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/CountingUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Counting Unit"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/CountingUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DimensionlessUnit> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/CurrencyUnit> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/CurrencyUnit> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "\n  Currency Units have their own subclass of unit because:\n   (a) they have additional properties such as 'country' and\n   (b) their URIs do not conform to the same rules as other units.\n  "^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#HTML> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/CurrencyUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/CurrencyUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Currency Unit"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/CurrencyUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DimensionlessUnit> .
_:autos327 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
_:autos327 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#allValuesFrom> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer> .
