<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DataItem> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DataItem> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "\n  <p>A <em>Data Item</em> holds a value that maybe a scalar or structured datatype.\n  <em>Quantity Value</em> specifies which case applies.\n  </p>"^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#HTML> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DataItem> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DataItem> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Data Item"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DataItem> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Concept> .
_:autos330 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
_:autos330 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#maxCardinality> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger> .
_:autos330 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/value> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DataItem> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:autos330 .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Datatype> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Datatype> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "\n   <p>A <em>Datatype</em> is a definition of the type of the \"value\" of a data item (for example, \"all integers between 0 and 10\"),\n   and the allowable operations on those values; the meaning of the data; and the way values of that type can be stored. \n  Some types are primitive - built-in to the language, with no visible internal structure.\n  For example \"Boolean\"; others are composite - constructed from one or more other types (of either kind).\n  For example lists, arrays, structures, unions. \n  Some languages provide strong typing, others allow implicit type conversion and/or explicit type conversion.\n  </p>"^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#HTML> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Datatype> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Datatype> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Datatype"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Datatype> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Concept> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DecimalPrefix> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DecimalPrefix> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "\n  A <em>Decimal Prefix</em> is a prefix for multiples of units that are powers of 10.\n  "^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DecimalPrefix> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DecimalPrefix> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Decimal Prefix"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DecimalPrefix> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Prefix> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DerivedUnit> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DerivedUnit> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "\n  <p>A <em>Derived Unit</em> is a type specification for units that are derived from other units.\n  </p>"^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#HTML> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DerivedUnit> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/dbpediaMatch> "http://dbpedia.org/resource/Category:SI_derived_units"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DerivedUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DerivedUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Derived Unit"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DerivedUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Unit> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DigitalCurrencyUnit> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DigitalCurrencyUnit> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "A currency-like unit for cryptographic or tokenized assets. Instances should reference an ISO 24165 Digital Token Identifier (DTI) when available."@en .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DigitalCurrencyUnit> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/informativeReference> <https://dtif.org/> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DigitalCurrencyUnit> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/informativeReference> <https://www.iso.org/standard/79891.html> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DigitalCurrencyUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A currency-like unit for cryptographic or tokenized assets. Instances should reference an ISO 24165 Digital Token Identifier (DTI) when available."@en .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DigitalCurrencyUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DigitalCurrencyUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Digital Currency Unit"@en .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/DigitalCurrencyUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/CurrencyUnit> .
