<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/ScaleType> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/ScaleType> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/plainTextDescription> "\n  Scales, or scales of measurement (or categorization) provide ways of quantifying measurements, values and other enumerated values according to a normative frame of reference. \n  Four different types of scales are typically used. \n  These are interval, nominal, ordinal and ratio scales.\n  "^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/ScaleType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/ScaleType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Scale type"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/ScaleType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/EnumeratedValue> .
