<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/SolidAngleUnit> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/SolidAngleUnit> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "\n  The solid angle subtended by a surface S is defined as the surface area of a unit sphere covered by the surface S's projection onto the sphere. \n  A solid angle is related to the surface of a sphere in the same way an ordinary angle is related to the circumference of a circle. \n  Since the total surface area of the unit sphere is 4*pi, the measure of solid angle will always be between 0 and 4*pi.\n  "^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/SolidAngleUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/SolidAngleUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Solid Angle Unit"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/SolidAngleUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/AngleUnit> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Statement> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Statement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Statement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Statement"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/Statement> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Statement> .
