<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/isDeltaQuantity> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "\n  This property is used to identify a Quantity instance that is a measure of a change, or interval, of some property,\n   rather than a measure of its absolute value. \n  This is important for measurements such as temperature differences where the conversion among units would be calculated differently because of offsets.\n  "^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/isDeltaQuantity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/isDeltaQuantity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "is Delta Quantity"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/isDeltaQuantity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/isoNormativeReference> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/isoNormativeReference> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Provides a way to reference the ISO unit definition."^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
