<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/standardUncertainty> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "The standard uncertainty of a quantity is the estimated standard deviation of the mean taken from a series of measurements."^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/standardUncertainty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy> <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/standardUncertainty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "standard uncertainty"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/standardUncertainty> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#decimal> .
